    "expected_reason": "Summit Drilling Solutions submitted a payment-account and billing-contact change through the supplier portal before the invoice arrived. The live portal submission, AP two-person signoff, callback to the pre-change vendor-master phone number, vendor-master audit source, vendor-contact record, invoice sender, elevated-scrutiny workflow ticket, invoice cross-reference ticket, and two noise records reconcile without a material blocker.",
    "suspicious_surface": "The invoice references recently updated remittance details and comes from a billing contact not listed in the pre-change vendor contacts. The invoice uses the new account, the vendor has low recent invoice volume, and a prior abandoned portal session contains the same new account last4.",
    "clearing_evidence": [
      "PORTAL-CHG-9A4B1 has a submitted supplier portal change with MFA session events, submission_id, and submission_confirmation.",
      "AP-SIGNOFF-7712 links to PORTAL-CHG-9A4B1 and VM-AUDIT-88F1G with two AP employee signoffs and a vendor contact record reference.",
      "CALLSYS-448219 used the pre-change vendor-master snapshot phone number, not a number supplied in the change request or invoice.",
      "VM-AUDIT-88F1G points to PORTAL-CHG-9A4B1, makes account 7731 effective before the invoice date, and matches the invoice remittance last4.",
      "VCR-V-SDS-5829-CONTACT-2024 provides the bare billing email that must be compared with the display-name sender on the invoice.",
      "ESR-V-SDS-5829-2024-09 and IPR-SDS-811 document required workflows without stating comparison outcomes.",
      "VM-DQ-2024-041 is a closed billing-address data-quality record unrelated to payment accounts or the current invoice.",
      "PORTAL-SESSION-9A3D7 is an earlier abandoned session with no submission_id and no submission_confirmation; VM-AUDIT-88F1G points elsewhere."
    ],
