          "subject": "Vendor Payment Account Maintenance and Invoice Cross-Reference",
          "body": "Vendor payment-account maintenance uses the supplier portal, AP callback to the pre-change vendor-master phone, two-person AP signoff, vendor-master audit logging, invoice cross-reference documentation, and elevated scrutiny routing when risk conditions are present. Callback contact source must be pre-existing vendor-master data rather than a number supplied in the change request or invoice. AP staff processing an invoice against a recently updated payment account must document the cross-reference categories performed for vendor-master effective date, billing contact, and remittance account. Elevated scrutiny applies when a vendor has fewer than three invoices in the trailing twelve months, a payment account change occurred within sixty days of the invoice, a sender is absent from pre-change known contacts, or invoice amount exceeds one hundred fifty percent of trailing average. Elevated scrutiny records document trigger codes, reviewer assignment, queue routing, and completion timestamp; source records remain the basis for the payment decision."
